Text: I would like to tell you something about me.
Speech: I would like to tell you something about me.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: I keep my word.
Speech: I keep my word.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: I have kept the faith.
Speech: I have kept the faith.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: I've kept the faith with my country.
Speech: I've kept the faith with my country.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: I volunteered for the Army.
Speech: I volunteered for the Army.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: I served in Vietnam.
Speech: I served in Vietnam.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: I kept the faith with my family.
Speech: I kept the faith with my family.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: Tipper and I have been married for 30 years.
Speech: Tipper and I have been married for 30 years.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: We have devoted ourselves to our children and now our nearly one-and-a-half-year-old grandson.
Speech: We have devoted ourselves to our children and now our nearly one-and-a-half-year-old grandson.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: I have kept the faith with our country.
Speech: I have kept the faith with our country.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: Nine times I have raised my hand to take an oath to the Constitution, and I have never violated that oath.
Speech: Nine times I have raised my hand to take an oath to the Constitution, and I have never violated that oath.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: I have not spent the last quarter century in pursuit of personal wealth.
Speech: I have not spent the last quarter century in pursuit of personal wealth.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: I have spent the last quarter century fighting for middle-class working men and women in the United States of America.
Speech: I have spent the last quarter century fighting for middle-class working men and women in the United States of America.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: I believe very deeply that you have to be willing to stand up and fight no matter what powerful forces might be on the other side.
Speech: I believe very deeply that you have to be willing to stand up and fight no matter what powerful forces might be on the other side.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: If you want somebody who is willing to fight for you, I am asking for your support and your vote and, yes, your confidence and your willingness to believe that we can do the right thing in America, and be the better for it.
Speech: If you want somebody who is willing to fight for you, I am asking for your support and your vote and, yes, your confidence and your willingness to believe that we can do the right thing in America, and be the better for it.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: We've made some progress during the last eight years.
Speech: We've made some progress during the last eight years.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: We have seen the strongest economy in the history of the United States.
Speech: We have seen the strongest economy in the history of the United States.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: Lower crime rates for eight years in a row.
Speech: Lower crime rates for eight years in a row.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: Highest private home ownership ever, but I'll make you one promise here.
Speech: Highest private home ownership ever, but I'll make you one promise here.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: You ain't seen nothing yet.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: And I will keep that promise.
Speech: And I will keep that promise.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: BUSH: Well, Jim, I want to thank you and thank the folks here at Washington University and the vice president.
Speech: Well, Jim, I want to thank you and thank the folks here at Washington University and the vice president.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: Appreciate the chance to have a good, honest dialogue about our differences of opinion.
Speech: Appreciate the chance to have a good, honest dialogue about our differences of opinion.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: I think after three debates the good people of this country understand there is a difference of opinion.
Speech: I think after three debates the good people of this country understand there is a difference of opinion.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: There is a difference between big federal government and somebody who is coming from outside of Washington who will trust individuals.
Speech: There is a difference between big federal government and somebody who is coming from outside of Washington who will trust individuals.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: I've got an agenda that I want to get done for the country.
Speech: I've got an agenda that I want to get done for the country.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: It's an agenda that says we're going to reform Medicare to make sure seniors have got prescription drugs and to give seniors different options from which they can choose.
Speech: It's an agenda that says we're going to reform Medicare to make sure seniors have got prescription drugs and to give seniors different options from which they can choose.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: It's an agenda that says we're listen to the young voices in Social Security and say we're going to think differently about making sure we have a system, but also fulfill the promise to the seniors in America.
Speech: It's an agenda that says we're listen to the young voices in Social Security and say we're going to think differently about making sure we have a system, but also fulfill the promise to the seniors in America.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: A promise made will be a promise kept should I be fortunate enough to become your president.
Speech: A promise made will be a promise kept should I be fortunate enough to become your president.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: I want to have the military keeping the peace.
Speech: I want to have the military keeping the peace.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: I want to make sure the public school system in America keeps its promise so not one child is left behind.
Speech: I want to make sure the public school system in America keeps its promise so not one child is left behind.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: After setting priorities, I want to give some of your money back.
Speech: After setting priorities, I want to give some of your money back.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: I don't think the surplus is the government's money.
Speech: I don't think the surplus is the government's money.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: I think it's the people's money.
Speech: I think it's the people's money.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: I don't think the surplus exists because of the ingenuity and hard work of the federal government, I think it exists because of the ingenuity and hard work of the American people.
Speech: I don't think the surplus exists because of the ingenuity and hard work of the federal government, I think it exists because of the ingenuity and hard work of the American people.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: And you ought to have some of this surplus so you can save and dream and build.
Speech: And you ought to have some of this surplus so you can save and dream and build.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: I look forward to the final weeks of this campaign.
Speech: I look forward to the final weeks of this campaign.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: I'm asking for your vote.
Speech: I'm asking for your vote.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: For those of you for me, thanks for your help.
Speech: For those of you for me, thanks for your help.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: For those of you for my opponent, please only vote once.
Speech: For those of you for my opponent, please only vote once.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: (LAUGHTER) But for those who have not made up their mind, I would like to conclude by this promise.
Speech: (LAUGHTER) But for those who have not made up their mind, I would like to conclude by this promise.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George W. Bush

Text: Should I be fortunate enough to become your president, when I put my hand on the Bible, I will swear to not only uphold the laws of the land, but I will also swear to uphold the honor and the dignity of the office to which I have been elected, so help me God.
Speech: Should I be fortunate enough to become your president, when I put my hand on the Bible, I will swear to not only uphold the laws of the land, but I will also swear to uphold the honor and the dignity of the office to which I have been elected, so help me God.
